genresAdvancedInfo.name: kansas hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Kansas hip hop is a style of hip hop that originated in the state of Kansas. It is characterized by its use of live instrumentation, including guitars, drums, and horns, as well as its socially conscious lyrics that often touch on themes of race, class, and politics. The sound is heavily influenced by jazz, blues, and soul, and is known for its raw, gritty energy.
